🔹 Ultimate DSA Cheat Sheet — Last-Minute Revision
1️⃣ Arrays
Patterns: Sliding window, prefix sum, two pointers, hashing
Must-Do:
Two Sum | Subarray Sum | Maximum Subarray (Kadane) | Trapping Rain Water | Product Except Self | Merge Intervals | Rotate Array | Majority Element | 3Sum / 3Sum Closest

2️⃣ Strings
Patterns: Sliding window, two pointers, string matching, DP on string
Must-Do:
Reverse Words | Palindrome Check / Longest Palindrome | Longest Substring Without Repeat | Min Window Substring | KMP / Rabin-Karp | Anagram Check | Valid Parentheses


3️⃣ Recursion & Backtracking
Patterns: Recursion tree, choice diagrams, backtracking
Must-Do:
N-Queens | Rat in Maze | Word Search | Subsets / Subset Sum | Permutations / Combinations | Sudoku Solver

4️⃣ Dynamic Programming
Patterns:
Subsequence DP: LIS, LCS, Shortest Common Supersequence
Interval DP: Matrix Chain Multiplication, Palindrome Partitioning, Burst Balloons
Knapsack DP: 0/1, Unbounded, Target Sum
Grid DP: Min Cost Path
Stocks DP: Buy/Sell variations
Must-Do: 0/1 Knapsack | Unbounded Knapsack | Target Sum | LIS / LCS | MCM | Palindrome Partition | Min Cost Path | DP on Stocks | Min Edit Distance


5️⃣ Linked List
Patterns: Two pointers, slow/fast pointer
Must-Do: Reverse List | Detect Cycle | Merge Two Sorted | Remove Nth Node | Intersection

6️⃣ Stack & Queue
Patterns: Monotonic stack, sliding window
Must-Do: Implement Stack/Queue | Next Greater/Smaller | Sliding Window Max | Evaluate RPN | Min Stack

7️⃣ Trees / BST
Patterns: DFS/BFS, recursion, divide & conquer
Must-Do: Traversals | LCA | Serialize/Deserialize | Diameter | Max Path Sum | Check Balanced | Kth Smallest/Largest BST | Build Tree from Inorder + Pre/Post

8️⃣ Heap / Priority Queue
Patterns: Top-K, sliding window
Must-Do: Kth Largest/Smallest | Merge K Sorted | Sliding Window Median | Top K Frequent

9️⃣ Graphs
Patterns: BFS, DFS, shortest path, cycle detection, MST
Must-Do: BFS/DFS | Detect Cycle | Dijkstra / Bellman-Ford | MST Prim/Kruskal | Topological Sort | Num of Islands | Word Ladder

🔟 Hashing / Maps / Sets
Patterns: Frequency maps, two pointers + hash, subarray sums
Must-Do: Two Sum / Subarray Sum | Count Distinct | Top K Elements | Subarray with 0 Sum

1️⃣1️⃣ Advanced / Misc
Patterns: Range queries, union-find, binary search variations
Must-Do: Union-Find / Disjoint Set | Segment Trees (Range Sum / Min / Max) | Fenwick Tree | Binary Search Variants | Sliding Window Problems

🔥 Last-Minute Tips
Focus Arrays → Strings → Recursion → Trees → DP first.
For DP, always identify pattern: subsequence / interval / knapsack / grid / stocks.
Use dry runs for recursion & DP problems.
For graphs, remember BFS for shortest path unweighted, DFS for cycles/components.
Keep STL cheat sheet ready: vector, set, map, unordered_map, priority_queue, stack, queue.
